@NODE Tooltypes "Tooltypes of icon"

                                @{b}@{u}TOOLTYPES:@{ub}@{uu}

 These  tooltypes  will  mainly be of @{b}no@{ub} interest for you since they can be
changed  using  the  appropiate  menu  commands  from  the @{"command window" LINK UseCmdWin}.
However,  some  internal  stuff  is  stored here to allow you to circumvent
problems with rather strange configurations of AmiTCP/IP.

 Note  that  all tooltypes marked by an asterix (*) will be modified by the
installer script if you perfrom an automatic configuration.
 You may not change them, later.

 @{u}Standard commodity tooltypes:@{uu}

  @{fg shine}DONOTWAIT      @{fg text}say workbench to continue booting when loading cdxNetLaunch
  @{fg shine}CX_PRI         @{fg text}commodity priority

 @{u}Again some of these (menu Preferences/Commodity settings/~):@{uu}

  @{fg shine}CX_HOTKEY      @{fg text}hotkey to open main window
  @{fg shine}CX_POPUP       @{fg text}open main window when started

 @{u}Configuration (menu Preferences/Configuration/Configuration):@{uu}

 @{fg shine}*SERIALDEVICE   @{fg text}name of serial.device (full path)
 @{fg shine}*SERDEVUNIT     @{fg text}unit
 @{fg shine}*IFACE          @{fg text}name of modem interface
 @{fg shine}*S2DEVICE       @{fg text}associated sana2.device
 @{fg shine}*S2DEVICEUNIT   @{fg text}its unit
 @{fg shine}*DOSTCPDEVICE   @{fg text}name of AmiTCP DOS device

 @{u}Configuration preferences (menu Preferences/Configuration/~):@{uu}

  @{fg shine}NOSANA2CHECK   @{fg text}don't check whether you are online
 @{fg shine}*CHECKDATES     @{fg text}compare date of my scripts & AmiTCP:bin/startnet;
                 disable if you don't have a battery backed up clock.
                 [will be disabled for manual configuration]
 @{fg shine}*NOTIFYSTARTNET @{fg text}disable if you don't want to automatically open the
                 configuration window when you change AmiTCP:bin/startnet
                 [will be disabled for manual configuration]

 @{u}Delay values (menu Preferences/Automatic operations/~):@{uu}

  @{fg shine}DELAY_QUITTCP  @{fg text}time to wait before stopnet
  @{fg shine}DELAY_OFFLINE  @{fg text}time to wait before offline
  @{fg shine}NEVER_QUITTCP  @{fg text};-)
  @{fg shine}NEVER_OFFLINE  @{fg text};-)

 @{u}Some internal variables (be careful !!!):@{uu}

  @{fg shine}ID_CMDTCPSTART @{fg text}name of program that initializes AmiTCP/IP;
                 cdxNetLaunch will deadlock if this doesn't match !
                 (default AmiTCP:bin/login)
 @{fg shine}*ID_STARTNET    @{fg text}full name of startnet file (AmiTCP:bin/startnet)
  @{fg shine}ID_SYSPROGDIR  @{fg text}path to AmiTCP commands (AmiTCP:bin)

 @{u}Script output (menu Preferences/IO window(s)/Define command IO):@{uu}

  @{fg shine}CMDOUTPUT      @{fg text}send script output here

 @{u}General stuff:@{uu}

  @{fg shine}PREFSDIR       @{fg text}where cdxNetLaunch saves data to
  @{fg shine}AMIGAGUIDEFILE @{fg text}where the guide is (requester will open if not found)
  @{fg shine}REFRESH_DELAY  @{fg text}delay to refresh main window gadgets.

 @{u}Additional:@{uu}

  @{fg shine}DISABLED       @{fg text}don't do anything on/off
  @{fg shine}REPORTS        @{fg text}report window
  @{fg shine}INITCMD        @{fg text}see @{"scripts" LINK Scripts}.
@ENDNODE

@remark -----------------------------------------------------------
@remark -----------------------------------------------------------

@NODE Info_AmiTCP "AmiTCP/IP from NSDi - copyright & distribution"
@TOC Main

                              @{b}@{u}WHAT IS AMITCP@{ub}@{uu}

 AmiTCP/IP the most used TCP/IP stack that is available for the Amiga.
 The TCP/IP standard (@{b}T@{ub}ransfer @{b}C@{ub}ontrol @{b}P@{ub}rotocol; @{b}I@{ub}nternet @{b}P@{ub}rotocol)
is needed to make a connection to other computers, networks or the internet
itself.  You need such a stack if you want to access the internet !
 Further  information  on  AmiTCP/IP  and TCP/IP itself can be found in the
@{"AmiTCP documentation" LINK AmiTCP:help/AmiTCP.guide/Main}.

                            @{b}@{u}WHERE TO GET AMITCP@{ub}@{uu}

 AmiTCP/IP is commercial software, but it is released as shareware in order
to make you able to try and evaluate it.
 A  copy  of  the  shareware  archive can be found on any aminet ftp-server
(directory comm/tcp) or on several CD-ROMs having been released.
 The   original,   licensed   software   package  including  the  software,
documentation  etc.   can  be  purchased from (nearly) every Amiga software
distributor around.

                       @{b}@{u}COPYRIGHT NOTES ABOUT AMITCP:@{ub}@{uu}

 Refer   to   the  file @{"AmiTCP:COPYRIGHTS" LINK AmiTCP:COPYRIGHTS/Main}  for  detailed information about
AmiTCP/IP and all copyrights concerning it !
 Please read the license file @{"AmiTCP:LICENSE" LINK AmiTCP:LICENSE/Main}, additionally !

 Here's the head entry of the COPYRIGHTS file:
@{fg shine}
All files in this AmiTCP/IP release, except ones noted in this file,
are:

	Copyright © 1994 AmiTCP/IP Group,
	                 NSDi - Network Solutions Development Inc., Finland.
	                 All rights reserved.

